1 d. Defines the outcome of an unsatisfactory review of post-tenured faculty, which
2 may be removal from the position. The decision to remove faculty from a position
3 must be made by the employing institution and the state board of higher
4 education.
5 e. Is approved by the state board of higher education.
6 2. Advertisement of open faculty positions by institutions of higher education under the
7 control of the state board of higher education offering faculty academic tenure must
8 designate the position as nontenure-track or tenure-track. Upon offering a tenure-track
9 position to a candidate, the institution shall provide the candidate the policy required
10 under this section.
